<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871110-0021 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Rio Algom Ltd.</HL><DD> 11/10/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> ROMTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   Rio Algom Ltd. said it agreed to merge with its Potash Co. of America unit under a proposed cash or stock transaction.    Rio Algom, which owns all of Potash's common shares, offered to buy Potash's 1.2 million preferred shares for 18 Canadian dollars each, or a total of 21.6 million dollars ($16.4 million). Alternatively, Rio Algom, a Toronto-based mining and specialty steel concern, offered Potash preferred holders the option of exchanging a preferred share for one Rio Algom common share. Rio Algom officials couldn't be reached for comment.    In trading yesterday on the Toronto Stock Exchange, Rio Algom closed at 16.50 dollars, down 25 cents. Potash's preferred shares last traded at 7.50 dollars on the Toronto exchange.    Rio Algom currently has 42.6 million common shares outstanding.    Rio Algom said it expects Potash preferred holders to vote on the proposed transaction in December. </TEXT></DOC>